text: Betsy Haines (born November 5, 1960) is an American cross-country skier. She competed in the women's 5 kilometres at the 1980 Winter Olympics. Haines is a University of Vermont graduate (class of 1984), and competed on the school's Nordic ski team. ==References== Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:American female cross-country skiers Category:Olympic cross-country skiers of the United States Category:Cross-country skiers at the 1980 Winter Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Salt Lake City Category:University of Vermont alumni Category:Vermont Catamounts skiers
